g.text: You: "No, I was listening to something."
Shivers: Of great importance to the few who attend.
Shivers: The great ghost of the air is holding its breath.
Kim Kitsuragi: "It is -- is that why we're stopping?"
Pain Threshold: Momentarily the sounds are swept away. Pain shoots up your right foot and into your groin...
Perception (Hearing): On the islet? There is almost no wind, just snow quietly falling on the reeds. Bulrushes swaying on the waterline, long dried leaves chafing against each other.
You: "It... hurts a bit. Maybe the bandage is off?"

Perception (Hearing): On the islet? There is almost no wind under the rain quietly falling on the reeds. Bulrushes swaying on the waterline, long dried leaves chafing against each other. The soft raindrops...
Perception (Hearing): A low hum. The air slowly moves through a concrete box -- through its ancient slits and cracks. Resonating. Hollow. A big building.
Perception (Hearing): Air flows out of a pillbox window. There is very little there. The air cossets flowers on a meadow? Absolute silence. Reeds motionless. Bulrushes motionless.
You: "Have you noticed how quiet it is?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "I have -- is that why we're stopping?"
Perception (Hearing): The far away roar of the city, distant like today's dream. Before it, the sound of sand. The low tide filtered through its grains... a bird tending to its feathers.
Perception (Hearing): The dry grass crackles under your feet as you stop. Far away birds' wings touch the still surface of the sea...
Perception (Hearing): A drop of rain falls on a black log. Of an extinguished camp-fire.
Conceptualization: Like a silent orchestra tuning -- at the beginning of some major work.
You: "It's really fucking silent on this island."
Kim Kitsuragi: "It can happen -- is that why we're stopping?"
You: "No, I was listening to something."
Pain Threshold: Momentarily the sounds are swept away. Pain shoots up your right foot and into your groin...
Perception (Hearing): On the islet? There is almost no wind, just the light movement of air through the reeds. Bulrushes swaying on the waterline, long dried leaves chafing against each other.
Perception (Hearing): A jitter. A sound impatient to happen, but not yet in this world.
Pain Threshold: This is where a lesser man would stop to think about the pain shooting up his right leg and into his groin -- not you, you're concentrated on how...
Perception (Hearing): Col Do Ma Ma Daqua.
You: "It's pretty silent on this island."
Pain Threshold: This is where a lesser man would stop to think about the pain shooting up his right leg and into his groin -- not you, you're concentrated on how...
You: "It's really fucking silent on this island."
You: "Have you noticed how quiet it is?"
Cuno: He squints at you. "Is that why we're stopping? So you can *bitch about the bandage*?"
Cuno: The kid shrugs. He sniffs, audibly -- then, silence.
You: "It's pretty silent on this island."
Logic: No, it's just your imagination. You can't hear such things.
Cuno: He shrugs. "Spooky-ass island. That's how it is on spooky-ass islands. Silent and shit."
Inland Empire: You hear some kind of limb fidget, producing an imperceptible tick...
You: "Mhm. Wait. I have to listen to one more thing."
You: "It... hurts a bit. Maybe the bandage is off?"
Perception (Hearing): A silent hiss, sea air moving through the needles of a pine tree.
Perception (Hearing): Raindrops fall on water, strangely quiet, forming circles in the distance...
Perception (Hearing): Snow falls on the water, melting away without even a whisper.
Perception (Hearing): The flock of quail departs; now more than a hundred metres away... a hundred and two... a hundred and five...
Cuno: "Fuckin' spooky, yeah. Is what it is."
You: "Mhm. Wait. I have to listen to one more thing."
Inland Empire: We are way out now... Way out in the West.
Cuno: "Yeah. Spooky-ass island. That's how it is on spooky-ass islands. Silent and shit."
Perception (Hearing): A flake of snow falls on an extinguished camp-fire. Hiss...
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant nods, in silence.
